    "created_at": "2015-07-22T07:26:38Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-07-22T07:26:38Z",
    "body": "> The new alert dialog no longer shows a close button (X). In most Windows apps, when you see a message box or a task dialog, it will have action buttons, but also the close button which is mapped to the default action (usually \"Cancel\" or \"OK\").\n\nThe TaskDialog API removes the close button when the dialog has a parent window, I don't see a flag to bring it back.\n\n> The default caption of the dialog is the executable name (e.g. \"electron.exe\"). I think it makes more sense to use \"productName\".\n\nI'm :+1: on this.\n\n> The style of the new dialogs is somewhat outdated (not \"clean and flat\" enough).\n\nThe `dialog` module is trying to be as native as possible, so if you want a more fashion dialog you should probably implement it yourself.\n"
  },
