    "updated_at": "2015-08-04T15:02:29Z",
    "body": "@zcbenz, thanks for taking care of the dialog caption issue :)\n\nWhat about the other issue regarding the missing close button:\n\n> The new alert dialog no longer shows a close button (X). In most Windows apps, when you see a message box or a task dialog, it will have action buttons, but also the close button which is mapped to the default action (usually \"Cancel\" or \"OK\").\n\nYou stated in one of your comments that:\n\n> The TaskDialog API removes the close button when the dialog has a parent window, I don't see a flag to bring it back.\n\nBut then I gave references from Microsoft official design guidelines that states that a task dialog must have a close button (see my previous comment). If the task dialog api doesn't have a flag to bring it up, then I guess it must be some style inherited from the parent.\n"
